From 8e9c2ce42891baa100ae90bdfc59929ac048fc73 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jun Zeng <jun1.zeng@intel.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Sep 2025 15:03:38 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Adaptive NVME SSD interrupt coalescing

1. do interrupt coalescing asyncly in thread;
2. check completed io num during the judgement of setting or clearing
interrupt coalescing;
3. refine the calling of adjust_coalesce in nvme_queue_rqs;
4. enable interrupt coalescing for write with req_size less than 32k;
5. record the nvme queues been used currently and only enable interrupt
coalescing when there are more than 2 nvme queues been used (can be modified
during runtime);
6. add debug variable to print the io info of used nvme queues.

Signed-off-by: Liang Fang <liang.a.fang@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jun Zeng <jun1.zeng@intel.com>
---
